[[!meta title="Accessibility"]]

Tails uses the <span class="application">GNOME Desktop</span> that
provides many accessibility features as documented in the [GNOME Access
Guide](http://library.gnome.org/users/gnome-access-guide/2.32/gnome-access-guide.html).
For a summary of those features, read the [quick
reference](http://library.gnome.org/users/gnome-access-guide/2.32/gnome-access-guide.html#quickref)
section of this guide.

To **hear screen elements spoken to you** or **magnify the screen**, see
the [GNOME
Orca](http://library.gnome.org/users/gnome-access-guide/2.32/gnome-access-guide.html#enable-orca)
section of this guide.

<div class="bug">
The screen reading functionality of <span class="application">GNOME
Orca</span> does not work neither with the <span
class="application">Iceweasel Web Browser</span> nor with the <span
class="application">Unsafe Web Browser</span>.
</div>

If you **prefer a pointing device over the keyboard**, you can use the
[[<span class="application">Florence</span> virtual
keyboard|first_steps/introduction_to_gnome_and_the_tails_desktop#florence]],
instead of the <span class="application">GNOME On-Screen
Keyboard</span>.

If you **are operating a computer with zero hands**, e.g.
by head-mouse or by eyetracker, you can use the <span
class="application">Dasher</span> graphical predictive text
input system.

If you **prefer high contrast, large print or inversed colors**, you can
change the default theme:

  0. Choose
     <span class="menuchoice">
       <span class="guimenu">System</span>&nbsp;▸
       <span class="guisubmenu">Preferences</span>&nbsp;▸
       <span class="guimenuitem">Appearance</span></span>.
  0. Select one of the theme to apply it. The following themes are
     available:
     - High Contrast
     - High Contrast Inverse
     - High Contrast Large Print
     - High Contrast Large Print Inverse
     - Large Print
     - Low Contrast
     - Low Contrast Large Print
  0. For large print themes, click the <span class="guilabel">Apply
     Font</span> to change the font size.
  0. Click <span class="guilabel">Close</span>.
